olive oil
1 carrot
1 courgette
1 Leek
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 packet Diced Chicken
¾ cup water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet couscous
1 packet flaked almonds
½ packet Apricot Sauce
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Thinly slice carrot and courgette into half-moons. Thinly slice leek.
• In a medium bowl, combine Mumbai spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Add diced chicken, season and toss to coat. Set aside.

• In a large saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook carrot, courgette and leek, stirring, until softened, 5-6 minutes.
• Add the water and chicken-style stock powder and a good pinch of salt and bring to the boil.
• Add couscous, then stir to combine. Cover with a lid and remove from heat. Set aside until water has absorbed, 5 minutes.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast flaked almonds, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a small bowl.
• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes. Remove from heat, then add apricot sauce (see ingredients) and a splash of water. Toss to coat.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Divide sauteed veggie couscous between bowls.
• Top with sticky-glazed Mumbai chicken.
• Top with Greek-style yoghurt and flaked almonds. Enjoy!